929833","title":"PSBs surpass private banks as quarterly profits reach new highs.\nOnly 3 of 30 listed universal banks had >1% net NPAs in Q3.","summary":"PSBs surpass private banks as quarterly profits reach new highs.\nOnly 3 of 30 listed universal banks had >1% net NPAs in Q3.","url":"https://www.business-standard.com/opinion/columns/psbs-outperform-private-peers-yet-again-as-quarterly-profits-hit-new-high-126022200380_1.html","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-02-22T15:50:37","source":"Business Standard"},{"id":"260127140070989","title":"RBI's revised PSL norms push banks towards direct lending, reducing reliance on NBFCs. External audits aim to curb misclassification and double counting.\nICICI Bank, HDFC Bank, and Axis Bank faced provisions due to PSL gaps. Total PSL book exceeds Rs 65 lakh crore, with MSME loans at Rs 31.3 lakh crore in FY25.","summary":"RBI's revised PSL norms push banks towards direct lending, reducing reliance on NBFCs. External audits aim to curb misclassification and double counting.\nICICI Bank, HDFC Bank, and Axis Bank faced provisions due to PSL gaps. Total PSL book exceeds Rs 65 lakh crore, with MSME loans at Rs 31.3 lakh crore in FY25.","url":"https://www.financialexpress.com/business/banking-finance-rbi-nudges-banks-towards-direct-priority-sector-lending-4120026/","imageUrl":null,"pubDate":"2026-01-26T23:27:00","source":"Financial Express"},{"id":"260121136269986","title":"Jammu & Kashmir Bank sees no immediate need for QIP despite board approval, citing steady credit growth and improved profits.\nThe bank reported a 10.7% YoY profit rise in Q3 FY25, with shares gaining over 8% in the past year.","summary":"Jammu & Kashmir Bank sees no immediate need for QIP despite board approval, citing steady credit growth and improved profits.\nThe bank reported a 10.7% YoY profit rise in Q3 FY25, with shares gaining over 8% in the past year.","url":"https://www.cnbctv18.com/market/earnings/jk-bank-in-no-rush-to-raise-capital-via-qip-as-profits-an